<div>

  <p style="font-weight: bold;">
    One more quick step!
  </p>

  <p>
    This study uses some data from Facebook to help us better
    understand the your answers to the survey. Just like your 
    survey answers, this data will be kept completely anonymous 
    and will not be shared with anyone. 
  </p>

  <%= form_tag url_for(:controller => 'surveyor', :action => 'create'), :id => 'create_survey_form' do %>
    <%= hidden_field_tag "survey_code", "redssocs" %>

    <div id="facebook_login_button" style="margin-top: 1em;">
      <fb:login-button 
        show-faces="false"
        scope="user_relationships,user_relationship_details,friends_relationships,friends_relationship_details"
        onlogin="$('#create_survey_form').submit()">
        Login with Facebook
      </fb:login-button>
    </div>
  <% end %>

  <p style="font-weight: bold;">
    What we are asking for and why:
  </p>

  <div>
    <ul>
      <li>Your friend list</li>
      <li>As much of the following basic information as is listed on your homepage:</li>
      <ul>
        <li>Birthday</li>
        <li>Gender, and</li>
        <li>Relationship status.</li>
      </ul>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p>
    We will use this data to ensure that our survey presents an unbiased view of Facebook 
    users in our inclusion group.
  </p>
    

  <p style="font-weight: bold;">
    How we plan to use this data:
  </p>

  <p>
    As part of this study, we will use methods from 
    <i>social network analysis</i>
    in order to analyze how patterns of behavior might be connected. 
    As with every other part of this study, your data will be kept 
    completely confidential, and your individual identity will never 
    be known or shared with anyone at any time.
  </p>
  
</div>
